Dialogue: 5,0:12:13.23,0:12:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying that after just drinking this...{TLC Implying she's a lightweight?}{he gave her juice, no alcohol in it. this line is purposefully vague so she doesnt catch his sarcasm. "this stuff is no big deal"}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:15.29,0:12:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's just plum wine, \Nit's alcohol all the same!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:18.10,0:12:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it sure is.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:20.50,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit trying to act like an adult.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:27.93,0:12:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Another!{Reminds me of the scene from Thor....}{another what}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:35.95,0:12:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel great.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:46.83,0:12:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I wanna go see Shioshishio.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.71,0:12:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll go after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.89,0:12:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Today,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:55.62,0:13:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari was talking to Manaka while she slept.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:02.35,0:13:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't come as too much of a shock, of course.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.84,0:13:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.73,0:13:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I doubt I'll have that look in my own eyes ever again.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:14.85,0:13:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have grown up physically,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:17.89,0:13:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems like I still haven't \Nmatured emotionally.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:21.61,0:13:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Does becoming an adult mean that you have to lose things?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:27.37,0:13:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There probably {\i1}is{\i0} a lot you wind up losing.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:30.43,0:13:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that just means you've gotta replace what you lost with something new.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:52.13,0:13:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,These last five years we've spent together have been like that for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:02.01,0:14:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not planning on doing anything more than that, are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:08.73,0:14:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:10.25,0:14:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We should get her to bed now, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:12.61,0:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lend me a hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.67,0:14:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.95,0:14:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I never did tell you, did I?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:20.17,0:14:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:21.67,0:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How grateful I was that you saved me\N at the Boatdrift Ceremony.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.65,0:14:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:27.61,0:14:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for you to be grateful.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.69,0:14:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And just to be clear, I'm not being modest or anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:32.67,0:14:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, \Nit really {\i1}did{\i0} cross my mind.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:36.73,0:14:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"If I just ignore him, \Nhe'll disappear forever."
Dialogue: 5,0:14:39.19,0:14:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"And then, I'll be able to be with Chisaki."
Dialogue: 5,0:14:42.54,0:14:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"Don't save him."
Dialogue: 5,0:14:43.96,0:14:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Just abandon him."
Dialogue: 5,0:14:46.07,0:14:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you dove in after me anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.63,0:14:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, if you had been able to do something like that,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:52.52,0:14:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never have let you be with Chisaki.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:55.83,0:14:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So the truth comes out.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:56.98,0:14:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:58.67,0:14:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:00.57,0:15:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am grateful that you guys came back.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:04.97,0:15:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Things have been up in the air this whole time.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:07.87,0:15:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, both Chisaki and I can move forward.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:21.85,0:15:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I drank so much, and yet I didn't get a hangover at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:26.99,0:15:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I'm pretty strong.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:30.07,0:15:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So from this point, I have to dive down seven meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:34.07,Some Boring Chalk #59,,0,0,0,,{\fax0.6\blur0.8\c&H78665C&\pos(157,105)\frz30.22\fscx107\fscy107\frx12\fry352}Directions to Shioshishio
Dialogue: 5,0:15:41.09,0:15:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have to face it...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:44.81,0:15:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:50.63,0:15:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This current is really strong.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:53.32,0:15:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Um...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:54.85,0:15:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What's going on?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.95,0:16:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Chisaki!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.05,0:16:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.49,0:16:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:37.58,0:16:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:39.85,0:16:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're usually so careful,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:42.25,0:16:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but sometimes you wind up \Nacting totally recklessly.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:45.42,0:16:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You think so?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:47.56,0:16:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:49.62,0:16:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:50.96,0:16:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I know we can reach it, \Nof course I'd come to see the village.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.16,0:16:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you've got a point there.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:58.11,0:17:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When he held me just now, it surprised me.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:02.09,0:17:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He didn't feel rugged at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:04.79,0:17:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was so different from the men I've had to examine as a nurse.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:09.71,0:17:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But of course he would be.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:11.56,0:17:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, his smile, his body, \Nand even his heart are...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:15.39,0:17:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're exactly the same as you were five years ago... aren't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:18.47,0:17:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:19.62,0:17:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you are.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:21.50,0:17:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For you, the Boatdrift Ceremony happened just the other day.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:26.06,0:17:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.44,0:17:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But you haven't changed either, you know.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:29.89,0:17:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the same Chisaki you always were.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:31.96,0:17:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:33.59,0:17:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd changed quite a bit.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:37.46,0:17:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, you haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:39.47,0:17:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You still look like you're listening while you're actually not listening at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:43.92,0:17:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:45.78,0:17:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you still get pissed off \Nwhenever I tease you in the least.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:49.65,0:17:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what about you, Hikari?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:51.70,0:17:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty early in the morning \Nfor you to be visiting here, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:55.28,0:17:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:56.81,0:18:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't stay put.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:03.41,0:18:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't stop wondering why Manaka's Ena disappeared.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:07.98,0:18:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I might be able to figure something out if I went back to where we found her.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:14.45,0:18:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:17.71,0:18:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if this will help or not,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:20.46,0:18:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but Tsumugu's grandfather told me a story.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:24.45,0:18:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the next part of the story about the sea god and the Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:28.10,0:18:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another part?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.63,0:18:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl who married the sea god \Neventually had children,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:35.20,0:18:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and their descendants flourished.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:38.77,0:18:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is said that as time passed,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.28,0:18:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the girl became more and more depressed.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:45.69,0:18:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She was sad that she'd left behind the one she loved on the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:52.19,0:18:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And since she could never forget about the man she loved,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:54.50,0:18:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,she could also never forget the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.97,0:19:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After learning of her sadness, the sea god tried desperately to make her happy.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:07.27,0:19:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he saw that she never truly would be,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:11.20,0:19:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he had no choice but to let her go back to the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:17.29,0:19:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he took something in return.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:21.43,0:19:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He took something?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:23.27,0:19:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking about it. \NMaybe that "something" was her Ena.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:33.29,0:19:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:41.35,0:19:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wooden Maiden...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:42.88,0:19:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Something in return for \Ngoing to the surface...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.29,0:19:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:49.36,0:19:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just a thought.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:51.18,0:19:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa also said this was passed down orally, \Nso he can't be sure how true it is.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:55.74,0:19:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.87,0:19:57.30,Alternative,,0,0,0,,{Huh?}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:58.57,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:59.55,0:20:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:01.02,0:20:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:02.54,0:20:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna find him and catch him.{by the toe?}{grab him?}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:05.85,0:20:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:07.95,0:20:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm positive he knows whether this part of the story is true.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:11.66,0:20:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it is, he'll probably know what needs to be done too!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.27,0:20:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I was out of ideas,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:19.91,0:20:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I know what I've gotta do.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:22.55,0:20:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Chisaki!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:24.73,0:20:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But man, the sea god's such a selfish jerk.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:28.77,0:20:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, taking people's Ena \Njust 'cause they don't obey him
Dialogue: 5,0:20:32.18,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then randomly \N{\alpha&HFF&}..{\r}giving other people Ena...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he, a kid?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:35.57,0:20:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:37.83,0:20:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe even after living for \Nhundreds and thousands of years,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:40.44,0:20:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he hasn't changed at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:42.82,0:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But I'm sure that's \Ngot nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:46.48,0:20:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about position or age. It's about your feelings.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:50.72,0:20:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Feelings?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:52.36,0:20:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait for Manaka to wake up.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.49,0:20:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna get her Ena back no matter what,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:57.54,0:21:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'm gonna help \NTsumugu with the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:01.76,0:21:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm never gonna give up!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:27.75,0:21:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh... I understand now.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:30.45,0:21:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I really do still like Hikari.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:38.17,0:21:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And this is how, after Manaka returned,
